headline: Google’s AI Progress Fuels MediaTek to Best Week Since 2002
summary: The stock is up more than 20% this week in Taipei, lifted by investor enthusiasm over Google’s latest Gemini model and AI chip deals.  MediaTek has reportedly partnered with the Alphabet Inc. unit on design of tensor processing units, now being seen as a potential rival to Nvidia Corp. chips in AI applications.  Known for its smartphone chips, MediaTek has suffered from a cloudy outlook for end-product demand as well as margin pressure due to competition and high development costs.

headline: 2025 was the year of AI, so who was the biggest winner?
summary: Yahoo Finance is putting a mirror up to 2025 and looking back on the biggest market stories, drivers, and stock outperformers. But only one can be named Yahoo Finance's Company of the Year. The search for this year's biggest winner has come down to three finalists: private artificial intelligence developer OpenAI (OPAI.PVT), semiconductor juggernaut Nvidia (NVDA), and enterprise cloud titan Oracle (ORCL). Yahoo Finance executive editor Brian Sozzi is joined by a panel of Envestnet Solutions Co-CIO and group president Dana D’Auria, Marketgauge.com chief strategist Michele Schneider, and Yahoo Finance senior reporter Ines Ferré, who each share their case for each prospective company in a year dominated by AI milestones and market catalysts. To watch more expert insights and analysis on the latest market action, check out more Opening Bid.
